ere.\n38\t\n39\tBoth axes share a single tag prefix (`v<axis-W-version>`) per release;\n40\tthe embedder-api crate carries its independent `version` field in its\n41\town `Cargo.toml`. Version-consistency checks (`set-version.sh\n42\t--check-files`) verify Axis W lockstep across all Axis-W manifests and\n43\tverify Axis E sits at its independently declared version.\n44\t\n45\t## Tiered publish order\n46\t\n47\tThe publish order is a strict topological sort of the workspace crate\n48\tdependency graph plus the two binding packages. Index-propagation sleeps\n49\tsit between tiers (pattern from pre-0.6.0 `.github/workflows/release.yml`).\n50\t\n51\t| Tier | Targets                                                      | Why                                                                                                                                                                 |\n52\t| ---- | ------------------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n53\t| T1   | `fathomdb-embedder-api`                                      | Leaf. Axis E. Must publish first so every later crate can resolve it on crates.io.                                                                                  |\n54\t| T2   | `fathomdb-schema`                                            | Leaf (no in-workspace deps beyond external crates).                                                                                                                 |\n55\t| T3   | `fathomdb-query`                                             | Depends on `fathomdb-schema` (per ADR-0.6.0-crate-topology consequences) and `fathomdb-embedder-api` indirectly via retrieval glue.                                 |\n56\t| T4   | `fathomdb-engine`                                            | Depends on T1+T2+T3. Largest crate; publishes only after its deps are resolvable on crates.io.                                                                      |\n57\t| T5   | `fathomdb-embedder`                                          | Depends on `fathomdb-embedder-api` (Axis E). Independent of `fathomdb-engine`.                                                                                      |\n58\t| T6   | `fathomdb`                                                   | Facade. Depends on `fathomdb-engine`.                                                                                                                               |\n59\t| T7   | `fathomdb-cli`                                               | Depends on `fathomdb` facade per ADR-0.6.0-crate-topology amendment 2026-05-11.                                                                                     |\n60\t| T8   | Python wheel (`src/python/`); TypeScript package (`src/ts/`) | Both wrap `fathomdb-engine` directly (PyO3 / napi-rs); they can publish in parallel after T4 resolves on crates.io. PyPI / npm publishing is independent of T5..T7. |\n61\t\n62\tCross-ecosystem gate: every tier must succeed before the next tier\n63\tstarts. `all-builds-passed` gates Tier T1 from starting until every\n64\tmatrix build for the release has produced an artifact (no \"publish T1\n65\twhile the napi-rs prebuild is still red\"). Cross-registry atomicity is\n66\tcovered by the post-publish smoke step below.\n67\t\n68\tTier inter-step sleep: keep the pre-0.6.0 60-second\n69\tcrates.io-index-propagation sleep between tiers. Without the sleep,\n70\tlater tiers race the index and fail dependency resolution.\n71\t\n72\t## Sibling-package co-tagging\n73\t\n74\tPer REQ-048, `fathomdb-embedder-api` and `fathomdb-embedder` carry the\n75\tsame git tag as the workspace release even though `fathomdb-embedder-api`\n76\truns on its own version axis. The tag prefix is workspace (Axis W);\n77\t`fathomdb-embedder-api` records its independent version inside the tag\n78\tcommit via its `Cargo.toml`.\n79\t\n80\t## Post-publish smoke\n81\t\n82\tPer `feedback_release_verification`, \"green CI + published wheel\" is not\n83\tdone. Release-evidence sweep installs the published wheel from PyPI and\n84\truns an end-to-end open + close + exit smoke before the release is\n85\tdeclared signed. Equivalent npm smoke applies for `@fathomdb/...`\n86\tpublishes. Crate publishes are smoked via `cargo install fathomdb-cli`\n87\tfollowed by `fathomdb doctor check-integrity --json` against a fresh\n88\tfixture database.\n89\t\n90\t## Sources\n91\t\n92\t- `dev/plans/ci-deferred.md` enumerates the pre-0.6.0 workflows being\n93\t  restored.\n94\t- `ADR-0.6.0-crate-topology` (incl. 2026-04-27 sibling amendment + 2026-05-11\n95\t  CLI-via-facade amendment) owns the crate set.\n96\t- `ADR-0.6.0-embedder-protocol` owns the `fathomdb-embedder-api` trait\n97\t  stability posture.\n98\t- REQ-047, REQ-048, REQ-049, REQ-050, REQ-052.\n99\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6c2ab885-f26f-4687-8076-7a046130c523","uuid":"c8648509-aa5f-4952-b512-85bf44c27cf4","timestamp":"2026-05-17T14:59:42.158Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-11d-release-workflow-20260517T145932Z/dev/design/release.md","content":"---\ntitle: Release Subsystem Design\ndate: 2026-05-12\ntarget_release: 0.6.0\ndesc: Version axes, tiered publish order, multi-registry publish discipline, and post-publish verification\nblast_radius: release workflows; REQ-047..REQ-052; scripts/set-version.sh; .github/workflows/release.yml; dev/plans/ci-deferred.md\nstatus: locked\n---\n\n# Release Design\n\nThis file owns release-gate mechanics: version axes, sibling-package\nco-tagging, tiered publish order, registry-installed smoke verification, and\natomic completion of the multi-registry publish flow.\n\n## Version axes (2026-05-12)\n\n0.6.0 ships **two independent version axes**, not one global workspace\nversion:\n\n- **Axis W (workspace).** Lockstep version for the runtime/binding/CL